However, we are in the southernmost part of Azerbaijan, just a few kilometres from the border with Iran.
Here live the "talyshi", a people about whom little is known, except that they are fluent in Persian and Azerbaijani and are very long-lived.
Our final destination is Lerik.
This small town boasts perhaps too massive a Soviet-era architecture that doesn't seem to fit in so nicely with the picturesque mountain landscape.
European tourists barely get to this place, as the road from Azerbaijan's capital, Baku, is too heavy.
