"I'll work two more years because I want to open a shop or study Spanish or French", he promises in a more than acceptable English.
Punished for life, this nice, intelligent young man might be a tour guide, a waiter, or a hotel receptionist, but instead he does the work of a mule.
Sharing a filthy wooden hut with other porters, he gets up every day at two in the morning because the sulfur keeps shining at night, when its characteristic yellow color turns blue and glows in the midst of darkness.
