I'm posting pictures of games or something.
I also entertain my acquaintances.
"I wouldn't share a photo that's not mine, or someone who's making a fool of himself", he says.
The child recognizes that it is wrong to post obscene pictures, of naked people, of crimes, or to write humiliating or violent comments.
Jorge claims to know the 35 friends he has on FB and his nine followers on Twitter.
Most of them are relatives.
The mother's included, she's got the key to one of the accounts.
I started Twitter to express myself and write interesting tweets.
"I don't know if they answer me, I just put them up", he adds.
"Social media is fun, I can talk to distant relatives or friends quickly", she says.
I'm sure you'll answer that I would never accept a request from a stranger.
I wouldn't listen to anyone who recommended a stranger.
The case of 14-year-old José is different.
