The state ranks fourth nationally in new and cumulative AIDS cases and 13th in HIV.
92% of infections are by sexual transmission, 6% by blood transmission and 2% by perinatal transmission.
It is estimated that 50,000 people may be living with HIV, as for every recorded case there are 4 to 5 people who do not know.
