Larry Hagman, whose role as predatory oil tycoon J.R. Ewing in the television series "Dallas" became a symbol of greed in the 1980s, has died.
He was 81.
Hagman, who returned this year as J.R. in a new season of "Dallas", died Friday afternoon due to complications from cancer, according to a family statement provided to The Associated Press by "Dallas" production house Warner Bros.
"Larry was back in his beloved hometown of Dallas, once again playing the iconic role he loved most", the family said.
Larry's family and his closest friends were with him in Dallas for the Thanksgiving holiday.
